      <lg type="edition">
<l>kalaiyuṇak kiḻinta muḻavumaruḷ perumpaḻañ</l>
<l>cilaikeḻu kuṟavark kalkumicai vāku</l>
<l>malaikeḻu nāṭa māvaṇ pāri</l>
<l>kalanta kēṇmaik kovvāy nīyeṟ</l>
<l>pulantaṉai yākuvai puranta yāṇṭē</l>
<l>peruntaku ciṟappi ṉaṭpiṟ kollā</l>
<l>toruṅkuvaral viṭāa toḻikeṉak kūṟi</l>
<l>yiṉaiyai yātali ṉiṉakku maṟṟiyāṉ</l>
<l>mēyiṉē ṉaṉmai yāṉē yāyiṉu</l>
<l>mimmai pōlak kāṭṭi yummai</l>
<l>yiṭaiyil kāṭci niṉṉō</l>
<l>ṭuṭaṉuṟai vākkuka vuyarnta pālē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>O man from a mountainousmountaineous land, (3ab)</l>
<l>where the drum-like big fruit that was torn open by a monkey to eat (1)</l>
<l>becomes lasting food for the bow-bearing hill people, (2)</l>
<l>  great generous Pāri (3cd)</l>
<l>you who are unequal to mutual intimacy (4)</l>
<l>are one who has become vexed with me. For the years you protected [me], (5)</l>
<l>[this] is not in agreement with a friendship of befitting great excellence. (6)</l>
<l>Without letting [me] come together [with you] you said “let him stay behind”, (7)</l>
<l>[and] because you are thus, to you I, however, (8)</l>
<l>am [still] attached, even though it may be in absence. (9)</l>
<l>Showing itself as in this birth, in the next birth [too] (10)</l>
<l>let lofty fate cause [me] to stay together (12)</l>
<l>with you of unimpeded sight. (11)  </l>
</lg>
